# GPU-fit tuning: Qwen3-Coder-Next Q5_K_M on 2x R9700 (MACHINE=r9700-dual).
#
# Sourced by run-vulkan.sh AFTER models/qwen3-coder-next.env and BEFORE
# profiles/r9700-dual/default.env. Holds only what depends on fitting this model's
# ~56 GiB of Q5_K_M weights in VRAM across both cards.
#
# All weights in VRAM => NO CPU-MoE offload (no --n-cpu-moe emitted here). Unlike
# the Q4_1 build, ~56 GiB of weights leaves little room for KV: only ~6 GiB across
# the 62 GiB pair. So context is trimmed hard and V-cache quantized. The knobs are
# tuned together to fit -- do not change one in isolation:
#   - CTX_SIZE=32768: as large as ~6 GiB of KV headroom allows at these quants.
#     This model's 2-KV-head GQA keeps 32K KV to ~1.7 GiB (q8_0 K / q4_0 V).
#   - UBATCH=512: keeps the per-GPU compute buffer small (~1-1.5 GiB).
#   - CACHE_TYPE_V=q4_0: halves V-cache; K stays q8_0 (launcher default). Flash-attn
#     is on by default, which quantized V requires.
# Budget: ~56 GiB weights + ~1.7 GiB KV + ~1.5 GiB compute ~= 59 GiB / 62 GiB.
# The margin is thin. If load OOMs: drop UBATCH to 256, then CTX_SIZE to 16384.
# For much more context, prefer the Q4_1 build (qwen3-coder-next-q4) which frees
# ~9 GiB of weights and reaches 256K.
: "${CTX_SIZE:=32768}"
: "${UBATCH:=512}"
: "${CACHE_TYPE_V:=q4_0}"
